# Taskr Environment Configuration
#
# Most users don't need this file! Taskr works out of the box with:
#   - SQLite database (auto-created at ~/.taskr/taskr.db)
#   - GitHub via `gh auth login` (recommended)
#
# This file is only needed for:
#   - CI/automation (use GITHUB_TOKEN)
#   - PostgreSQL databases (better search performance)

# ============================================
# GITHUB (CI/Automation only)
# ============================================
# For local development, use `gh auth login` instead (more secure).
# Only set GITHUB_TOKEN for CI pipelines or automation.
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxx

# ============================================
# DATABASE (Optional)
# ============================================
# Default: SQLite at ~/.taskr/taskr.db (zero config)
#
# For PostgreSQL (enables full-text search, better performance):
# TASKR_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/taskr

# ============================================
# IDENTITY (Optional)
# ============================================
# TASKR_AUTHOR=yourname
# TASKR_AGENT_ID=claude-code

# ============================================
# QUICK START
# ============================================
#
# 1. Install taskr:
#    pip install taskr-mcp
#
# 2. Authenticate with GitHub (one-time):
#    gh auth login
#
# 3. Run the MCP server:
#    python -m taskr_mcp
#
# That's it! SQLite database auto-creates, gh handles GitHub auth.
